Moreover: that there is ſuch an impreſſion of a God naturally; appeares from the Devills themſeves, who believe and tremble; and from the moſt1 King. 17.30, 31. paganiſh and moſt barbarous people, and nations, who have acknowledged ſome god or other; and worſhipt him accordingly. As the Sun, the Moone, the ſtarres, ſome Freind or Benefactour;

ſome beaſt or other, that has been profitable to them;Naſcuntur in bortis numina. or elſe their very leekes and onions, or if they knew not what God to worſhip in particular; rather then they would owne no God at All, they Inſcribed their Altars 
